Start RabbitMQ Service: Run the following command to start the RabbitMQ service:

sudo systemctl start rabbitmq-server


Enable RabbitMQ to Start on Boot: If you want RabbitMQ to automatically start when the system boots, use:
sudo systemctl enable rabbitmq-server


Check RabbitMQ Service Status: To verify that RabbitMQ is running, use:

sudo systemctl status rabbitmq-server


Access RabbitMQ Management Dashboard (Optional): If you installed the RabbitMQ management plugin, you can access the web UI:


sudo rabbitmq-plugins enable rabbitmq_management


